{
  "name": "WF: Email Finder V2 (Catch-All Probe)",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Email Finder V2 — Orchestrator\n**Trigger:** POST /webhook/wf-email-finder-v2\n\n**Modes:**\n- `mode:name` — generate 10 patterns from first_name + last_name + domain\n- `mode:verify` — verify a single email address\n- `mode:probe` — skip SMTP, directly probe via burner email (same inputs as name)\n- `mode:recheck` — re-query email_probe_bounces for existing candidates (pass candidates[] + domain)\n\n**SMTP path (name/verify):** Execute Workflow → SUB — SMTP Check → if NOT catch-all → return SMTP results\n**Probe fallback:** If catch-all → HTTP Request → SUB — Burner Probe (300s timeout)\n**Direct probe (mode=probe):** Skip SMTP entirely → HTTP Request → SUB — Burner Probe\n**Recheck path:** Query email_probe_bounces directly (no SMTP/probe)\n\n**Sub-workflows:**\n- `SUB — SMTP Check` — executeWorkflow (sync)\n- `SUB — Burner Probe` — webhook at /webhook/sub-burner-probe (HTTP call, ~4 min)",
        "height": 240,
        "width": 620,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "wfefv2-sticky",
      "name": "Sticky Note",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -220,
        120
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "wf-email-finder-v2",
        "responseMode": "responseNode",
        "options": {},
        "authentication": "headerAuth"
      },
      "id": "wfefv2-0001",
      "name": "Webhook Trigger",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        0,
        400
      ],
      "webhookId": "wf-email-finder-v2",
      "credentials": {
        "httpHeaderAuth": {
          "id": "Jvj4HIG7aE6YPKcJ",
          "name": "Webhook Header Auth"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "mode": "runOnceForEachItem",
        "jsCode": "const body = $input.item.json.body || $input.item.json;\nconst mode = (body.mode || 'name').trim();\n\nfunction normName(s) {\n  return (s || '').normalize('NFD').replace(/[\\u0300-\\u036f]/g, '').toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]/g, '');\n}\n\nlet domain = '';\nlet candidates = [];\n\nif (mode === 'recheck') {\n  candidates = Array.isArray(body.candidates) ? body.candidates : [];\n  domain = (body.domain || '').trim().toLowerCase();\n} else if (mode === 'verify') {\n  const email = (body.email || '').trim().toLowerCase();\n  domain = email.split('@')[1] || '';\n  candidates = email ? [email] : [];\n} else {\n  // name or probe mode — generate email patterns from name + domain\n  const raw = (body.domain || body.website || '').trim();\n  domain = raw.replace(/^https?:\\/\\//i, '').replace(/^www\\./i, '').split('/')[0].trim().toLowerCase();\n  const f = normName(body.first_name);\n  const l = normName(body.last_name);\n  if (f && l) {\n    candidates = [\n      f + '.' + l + '@' + domain,\n      f[0] + '.' + l + '@' + domain,\n      f + '@' + domain,\n      l + '@' + domain,\n      f + l + '@' + domain,\n      l + f + '@' + domain,\n      l + '.' + f + '@' + domain,\n      f[0] + '_' + l + '@' + domain,\n      f + '_' + l + '@' + domain,\n      (f[0] + (l[0] || '')) + '@' + domain\n    ];\n  } else if (l) {\n    candidates = [l + '@' + domain];\n  } else if (f) {\n    candidates = [f + '@' + domain];\n  }\n  const seen = new Set();\n  candidates = candidates.filter(c => { if (seen.has(c)) return false; seen.add(c); return true; });\n}\n\nreturn { json: { mode, domain, candidates } };"
      },
